  "text": "HIV-infected subject sample selection. Serum samples from HIVinfected subjects not on ART and in early infection were obtained from the Baltimore-Washington, DC, site of MACS. MACS is an ongoing prospective cohort study of the natural and treated history of HIV infection in men who have sex with men at 4 sites in the US (Baltimore, Maryland/Washington, DC; Chicago, Illinois; Los Angeles, California; and Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania) [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . MACS participants are followed with semi-annual study visits that include questionnaires, a brief physical exam, and phlebotomy for laboratory tests and storage of serum, plasma, and peripheral blood mononuclear cells. HIVuninfected participants are tested at each visit for HIV seroconversion.",
